Text: 3/7Was placed into our teams today.
Looking forward to working with new people.
Also, got given the project list and there is some interesting projects to choose from.
Decided to come together on Sunday evening t=with personal choices for the project.
4/7Spent some time investigating the different projects to see which ones I preferred.
5/7Spent more time investigating projects.
Decided my favourites were Maddcog and Winely.
I was interested in the SDHB project but unfortunately, one of my teammates was not interested at all.
6/7We met at 9am today but were missing a teammate.
Early communication hiccups to be sorted out.
We met again at 12pm and the same teammate was late so hopefully sort out these issues early on.
Unfortunately, one person is not interested in using any form of communication other than email or text which we will have to workaround.
Did a lot of research on MaddCogg as that was our teams first choice with Winely as the second choice for the project pitch.
Started working on preparing our pitch.
7/7Finalised our pitch today and presented it.
It seemed to go well despite us choosing not to use any slides.
We missed out on our first choice so had to compromise and go with our second choice, Winely which I am fine with as they were pretty equal in my preference and the other I believe.
One teammate had to move to another group as he changed his mind about our second choice and was not very keen.
They are now getting to do the MaddCog project which works out best for everyone.
8/7We worked on researching Winely and the surrounding technologies as we had focussed on MadCog before.
Started to prepare for our interview with the client.
9/7More research and met to discuss before the interview with the client.
Looks like it is an interesting project and we have a range of knowledge and skills in this team.
Met with the client which went well.
The project looks to be simpler than we first thought but does have room for us to put our own spin on it and add detail, especially around the interface.
10/7Had the Shift meeting and did a workshop on Software Engineering/Development.
It was very interesting and useful and hopefully, we can use some of the knowledge and skills on the current project.
11/7Had a day off today.
12/7The team met with the client today but unfortunately was unable to attend.
Sounds like it was productive, so looking forward to hearing about it tomorrow.
